headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 22 points before leaving the game with a sprained ankle in the third quarter, and the NBA-leading Utah Jazz beat the Indiana Pacers 119-111 on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Minus injured Mitchell, Jazz rally to beat Pacers 119-111

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Detroit Pistons

headlines.description: — Josh Jackson scored 29 points, and the Detroit Pistons overcame several key absences to beat Oklahoma City 110-104 on Friday night, handing the Thunder their ninth straight loss.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pistons hand Thunder 9th straight loss with 110-104 victory

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had 36 points and 14 rebounds and the Philadelphia 76ers beat the Clippers 106-103 on Friday night, snapping Los Angeles' seven-game winning streak.

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Washington Wizards

headlines.description: — Russell Westbrook scored 10 of Washington's 12 points in overtime, including a pair of free throws to break a tie with just one second left after he was fouled by Zion Williamson, and the Washington Wizards edged the New Orleans Pelicans 117-115...
headlines.shortLinkText: Westbrook's OT foul shots after Zion foul lift Wiz past Pels

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant had 25 points and 11 assists, Joe Harris scored 26 points and the Brooklyn Nets beat the Charlotte Hornets 130-115 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant, Harris lead Nets to 130-115 win over Hornets

headlines.description: — Paul Watson Jr. scored 20 of his career-high 30 points in the third quarter Friday night and the Toronto Raptors pulled away to a 113-102 victory over the Orlando Magic.
headlines.shortLinkText: Watson, Watanabe lead Raptors past Magic, 113-02

headlines.description: — Dylan Brooks scored a season-high 32 points and the Memphis Grizzlies took control in the second half to beat the Chicago Bulls 126-115 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brooks scores 32, Grizzlies pull away to beat Bulls 126-115

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic scored 29 points, Michael Porter Jr. added 21 and the Denver Nuggets cruised to a 128-99 victory over the Houston Rockets on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic, Porter help Nuggets cruise by Rockets, 128-99

headlines.description: — Karl-Anthony Towns scored 24 points, including eight in the fourth quarter before fouling out, to lead the Minnesota Timberwolves to a 119-111 win against the Miami Heat on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Towns scores 24, helps Timberwolves beat Heat 119-111

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — CJ McCollum scored 29 points and the Portland Trail Blazers escaped with a 107-106 victory Friday night over the San Antonio Spurs, who missed three shots on their final possession.
headlines.shortLinkText: McCollum, Trail Blazers escape with 107-106 win over Spurs

events.name: New York Knicks at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Julius Randle scored 44 points in his best game in his hometown, leading the New York Knicks to a 117-109 victory over the Dallas Mavericks on Friday night for a five-game winning streak, their longest in seven years.
headlines.shortLinkText: Randle scores 44 in hometown, Knicks beat Mavs 117-109
